 read.csv('input/meta.csv', row.names = 1)\\ndesign <- model.matrix(~ 0 + meta$group)\\ncolnames(design) <- levels(meta$group)\\nfit <- lmFit(exprs, design)\\ncontrast.matrix <- makeContrasts(cancer - normal, levels = design)\\nfit2 <- contrasts.fit(fit, contrast.matrix)\\nfit2 <- eBayes(fit2)\\ntopTableResults <- topTable(fit2, adjust = 'fdr', number = 250)\\nwrite.csv(topTableResults, 'output/deg_results.csv')\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "next_agent_state": {"tools": [{"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_shell", "description": "Run a shell command in the task work_dir (bash -lc).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"command": {"description": "Shell command string passed to `bash -lc`.", "title": "Command", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["command"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "read_text_file", "description": "Read a UTF-8 text file relative to work_dir.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["relative_path"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "write_text_file", "description": "Write text to a path under work_dir (creates parent dirs).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}, "content": {"description": "Full file body to write as UTF-8 text.", "title": "Content", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["relative_path", "content"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_rscript", "description": "Run inline R code via Rscript -e (single line safe for agents).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"code": {"description": "R expression passed as the argument to `Rscript -e`.", "title": "Code", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["code"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "list_workdir", "description": "List workspace as JSON (bounded depth).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": []}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "write_plan", "description": "Persist a markdown plan to `workspace/.plan.md` (overwrite on rewrite).\n\nUse this at the start of a task and whenever the plan needs revision. The\nplan is not shown automatically on later steps; call check_progress to see\nthe current plan excerpt alongside deliverable state.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"plan": {"description": "Markdown text describing the step-by-step plan (bullet list).", "title": "Plan", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["plan"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "check_progress", "description": "Log a progress note and return a JSON snapshot of deliverables + plan excerpt.\n\nAppends `<UTC ISO timestamp> <note>` to `workspace/.progress.log`, then\nreturns a JSON string containing:\n  - `output_files`: list of {name, size_bytes} under `workspace/output/`.\n  - `success_artifact_present`: whether the task's success artifact glob matches.\n  - `plan_excerpt`: first 1000 chars of `.plan.md` (or empty if missing).\n  - `note_count`: total notes logged so far.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"note": {"description": "Short progress note to append to the log (plain text, one line).", "title": "Note", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["note"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "submit_done", "description": "End the episode. Set success=true only if criteria met (agent-declared).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"success": {"description": "Whether the agent believes the task objective is satisfied.", "title": "Success", "type": "boolean"}, "summary": {"default": "", "description": "Short optional note for logging.", "title": "Summary", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `riya_limma`\n\n# Real R-task: riya_limma\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `RiyaDua-cervical-cancer-snakemake-workflow` (family: `rna`, stage: `late`, difficulty: `2`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given `input/exprs.csv` (pre-normalised, row = probe, column = sample)\nand `input/meta.csv` with a `group` column (`cancer` vs `normal`). Use limma\n(`lmFit` + `makeContrasts(cancer - normal)` + `eBayes`) to compute the top 250\nDE probes (`topTable(..., adjust='fdr', number=250)`) and save to\n`output/deg_results.csv` via `write.csv(...)`. Do NOT produce a volcano plot.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/deg_results.csv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: deg_results.csv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"exprs.csv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"exprs.csv\"\n    },\n    \"meta.csv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"meta.csv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/deg_results.csv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_CjrOHzLtKt1menHnqZq4bi2D", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary libraries, specifically the limma package.\\n2. Read the expression data from 'input/exprs.csv' and the metadata from 'input/meta.csv'.\\n3. Create a design matrix using the group column from the metadata.\\n4. Fit a linear model to the expression data using the lmFit function.\\n5. Define the contrast of interest (cancer vs normal) using the makeContrasts function.\\n6. Apply the contrast to the fitted model using the contrasts.fit function.\\n7. Compute empirical Bayes statistics using the eBayes function.\\n8. Extract the top 250 differentially expressed probes using the topTable function with FDR adjustment.\\n9. Write the results to 'output/deg_results.csv'.\\n10. Verify the output file exists and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (744 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_CjrOHzLtKt1menHnqZq4bi2D"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_UZnxy7wmtjDJyvB7mpmYcYkM", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(limma)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}, {"id": "call_eA3ibOhpbVhN26ZYv0in5omq", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/exprs.csv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_b2njqdlwgK0jNjuku6tQSZP1", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/meta.csv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=0\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\n", "name": "run_rscript", "tool_call_id": "call_UZnxy7wmtjDJyvB7mpmYcYkM"}, {"role": "tool", "content": ",GSM0001,GSM0002,GSM0003,GSM0004,GSM0005,GSM0006,GSM0007,GSM0008\nPROBE_00000,10.4568,10.4481,10.4666,10.7106,7.9617,7.5508,8.0997,7.9198\nPROBE_00001,7.9349,8.0348,8.0697,8.3491,8.1970,8.0332,7.7785,7.6956\nPROBE_00002,8.0739,8.3933,8.0125,7.9681,8.1595,7.5639,7.9063,8.1471\nPROBE_00003,8.2620,7.9278,8.1130,8.0745,8.2347,7.6660,8.1705,7.5456\nPROBE_00004,7.2140,7.8179,7.7253,8.2628,8.1993,7.6343,8.2542,7.6993\nPROBE_00005,7.9741,7.9118,8.0343,8.2456,8.1915,8.1050,8.1950,8.1435\nPROBE_00006,7.8119,7.7848,7.8590,8.1498,7.9250,8.7007,7.7542,7.6703\nPROBE_00007,8.2305,8.4266,8.1517,8.2507,8.4279,7.9718,7.5731,7.8404\nPROBE_00008,8.2859,7.5669,8.0101,8.0760,7.9053,8.2171,8.1742,8.6964\nPROBE_00009,8.1860,7.8172,7.8315,7.7505,8.285