reate a design matrix using the group column from the metadata.\\n4. Fit a linear model to the expression data using the lmFit function.\\n5. Define the contrast of interest (cancer vs normal) using the makeContrasts function.\\n6. Apply the contrast to the fitted model using the contrasts.fit function.\\n7. Compute empirical Bayes statistics using the eBayes function.\\n8. Extract the top 250 differentially expressed probes using the topTable function with FDR adjustment.\\n9. Write the results to 'output/deg_results.csv'.\\n10. Verify the output file exists and submit the task as complete.\",\n  \"note_count\": 1\n}", "name": "check_progress", "tool_call_id": "call_F7QZPOpWG3t6sy0oQwHq3R44"}], "action": {"call_id": {"run_id": "f106c776-9e98-43b5-970e-faee443fdad2", "fwd_id": "1229fe86-a1e9-4862-a8c7-9a2a7531e744"}, "op_name": "_llm_call_op", "op_class_name": "ldp.graph.common_ops.LLMCallOp", "value": {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_F7QZPOpWG3t6sy0oQwHq3R44", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"note\": \"Differential expression analysis completed and results saved to 'output/deg_results.csv'.\"}", "name": "check_progress"}}]}, "logprob": null}, "reward": 0.0, "truncated": false, "done": false, "value": 0.0, "metadata": {}}
